article.headline: Siena 76, Marist 72
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Alex Franklin scored a game-high 20 points to lead Siena to a 76-72 win over Marist Monday, bringing the Saints within a game of Rider for first place in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference. Edwin Ubiles scored 15 points for Siena (14-8, 9-3 MAAC), continuing his streak of scoring in double figures every game this season. Tay Fisher added 14 points for Siena and Kenny Hasbrouck had 10. Franklin scored the Saints' first 10 points of the game and eight of their first 10 points of the second half. Six of his points were from the free-throw line. Siena led for virtually the entire game and was ahead 37-34 at halftime. David Devezin, Jay Gavin, and Ryan Schneider each had 15 points for Marist (14-9, 8-4).
